Round 1: 
[Patient] Can you recommend exercises for me? 
[Educator] Walking and gentle stretching can help your heart. Start slow and listen to your body.

Round 2: 
[Patient] Are there any exercises I should avoid? 
[Educator] Avoid high intensity workouts. Focus on low impact activities like swimming or biking.

Round 3: 
[Patient] How often should I exercise? 
[Educator] Aim for 30 minutes of exercise most days of the week. Take breaks when needed.

Round 4: 
[Patient] Can I lift weights to exercise? 
[Educator] Light weights can be beneficial, but avoid heavy lifting. Focus on proper form.

Round 5: 
[Patient] Should I do yoga for exercise? 
[Educator] Yoga can be great for flexibility and relaxation. Just listen to your body's limits.

Round 6: 
[Patient] Can I do cardio exercises like running? 
[Educator] Running may be too strenuous. Consider brisk walking or using an elliptical machine.

Round 7: 
[Patient] What about group exercise classes? 
[Educator] Group classes can be fun and motivating. Look for low impact options like water aerobics.

Round 8: 
[Patient] Can I do exercise at home? 
[Educator] Yes, there are plenty of home workout videos available online. Just make sure to stay safe.

Round 9: 
[Patient] How can I stay motivated to exercise? 
[Educator] Find a workout buddy or set specific goals. Celebrate small victories along the way.

Round 10: 
[Patient] Thank you for the exercise recommendations. 
[Educator] You're welcome! Remember to listen to your body and make exercise a regular part of your routine.